publicationXrefb27.standardName: Insulin signalling and the regulation of glucose and lipid metabolism.

publicationXrefd3b.standardName: A mathematical model and computer simulation study of insulin sensitive glucose transporter regulation.

pathway.author: [MaintBot, Zari, Mkutmon, Eweitz]

comments.content: Insulin signaling influences energy metabolism as well as growth. The presence of insulin signals the fed state, and this signal is passed via the AKT branch, which leads to the uptake of glucose from the blood. Other branches of the signal cascade lead to cell growth and differentation.
This pathway was inferred from Homo sapiens pathway [http://wikipathways.org/instance/WP481_r94171 WP481 (r94171)] with a 98.0% conversion rate.
